can you help me decrease the size of this toggle a little bit?

I don't see any toggle or code in your message. Could you please share the HTML/CSS code you're working with? Once you do, I'll be happy to help you adjust its size.
```css components/Toggle/Toggle.css
:root {
    --primary-color: #287891;
    --secondary-color: #ffffff;
    --tertiary-color: transparent;
    --font-size-compact: 12px;
    --font-size-default: 1.25rem;
    --font-weight-default: normal;
    --padding-compact: 6px 10px;
    --padding-default: 10px 10px;
    --border-radius: 2em;
    --text-color: #333;
    --border-color: #333;
}

.toggle {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: background 0.2s;
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle {
    width: 50px;
    height: 30px;
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle-switch {
    height: 22px;
    width: 22px;
    left: 4px;
    bottom: 4px;
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle-checkbox:checked + .toggle-label .toggle-switch {
    transform: translateX(20px);
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle {
    width: 40px;
    height: 24px;
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle-switch {
    height: 18px;
    width: 18px;
    left: 3px;
    bottom: 3px;
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle-checkbox:checked + .toggle-label .toggle-switch {
    transform: translateX(16px);
}

.toggle-checkbox {
    opacity: 0;
    width: 0;
    height: 0;
}

.toggle-label {
    position: absolute;
    cursor: pointer;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background-color: #ccc;
    transition: .4s;
    border-radius: 34px;
}

.toggle-switch {
    position: absolute;
    content: "";
    background-color: white;
    transition: .4s;
    border-radius: 50%;
}

.toggle-checkbox:checked + .toggle-label {
    background-color: #287891;
}

.toggle-label:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 0 1px #2196F3;
}

.toggle-checkbox:focus + .toggle-label {
    box-shadow: 0 0 1px #2196F3;
}

.toggle-checkbox:disabled + .toggle-label {
    opacity: 0.6;
    cursor: not-allowed;
}

.toggle-container {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle-text {
    font-size: var(--font-size-compact);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-compact);
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle-text {
    font-size: var(--font-size-default);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-default);
}

.toggle-text {
    color: #333;
    user-select: none;
    font-family: "Roboto", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}
```

can you help me decrease the size of this toggle a little bit?

I'll help you make the toggle smaller. Here's the modified CSS with reduced sizes for both the default and compact variants:

```css
/* For the default size */
.toggle-container.default .toggle {
    width: 44px;  /* Reduced from 50px */
    height: 26px; /* Reduced from 30px */
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle-switch {
    height: 20px;  /* Reduced from 22px */
    width: 20px;   /* Reduced from 22px */
    left: 3px;     /* Adjusted from 4px */
    bottom: 3px;   /* Adjusted from 4px */
}

.toggle-container.default .toggle-checkbox:checked + .toggle-label .toggle-switch {
    transform: translateX(18px); /* Adjusted from 20px */
}

/* For the compact size */
.toggle-container.compact .toggle {
    width: 34px;  /* Reduced from 40px */
    height: 20px; /* Reduced from 24px */
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle-switch {
    height: 16px;  /* Reduced from 18px */
    width: 16px;   /* Reduced from 18px */
    left: 2px;     /* Adjusted from 3px */
    bottom: 2px;   /* Adjusted from 3px */
}

.toggle-container.compact .toggle-checkbox:checked + .toggle-label .toggle-switch {
    transform: translateX(14px); /* Adjusted from 16px */
}
```

I've made these changes:
1. Reduced the overall toggle width and height
2. Reduced the switch (circle) size
3. Adjusted the positioning and translation values to match the new sizes

These changes will make both the default and compact versions of the toggle slightly smaller while maintaining their proportions. You can further adjust these values if you want it even smaller or if you need to fine-tune the sizes.
